##What a surprise! A bunch of high school kids and a bunch of 95s are helping them with their face masks

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

"sanitation workers still need attention. " A group of high school students created the "Mask Shenzhen" project, and a group of university students created the "Mask Zhuhai" project, hoping to help sanitation workers during the epidemic.

By Gan Linan, Jiang minyu, and Chen Ganbo | Adzuki

More than five o'clock in the morning in Shenzhen, the day is not bright enough, Weiqiang sanitation workers are ready to go out. He pulled a folded disposable surgical mask from his jacket pocket and put it on.

The two masks issued by the company years ago have already been used up, selling for 4.5 yuan a disposable mask, Weiqiang reluctant to use only once. He pressed the top bar of the mask along the outline of his face, as he had learned on television, and the mask he had been wearing for two days gave off a faint odor.

The concerns of the sanitation workers

"I don't even want to do it. I have to pull so much garbage every day. Who knows if it belongs to a sick person or a healthy person? If I catch the garbage from a sick person, it's not worth it. " Wuhan had been closed off for a week at the time, as the COVID-19 continued to spread across the country, his anxiety grew and his desire to resign grew.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Poorly protected sanitation workers at work (Source: Zhuhai Environmental Health Association)

Xuehua, a beijing-based sanitation worker, has run to several supermarkets and pharmacies, unable to buy masks and disinfectants, and two cotton masks issued by the Union years ago are said to be dust-proof. When she returns to her rental home from work each day, all she can do is as the company tells her to do -- Wash her hands.

Feng Ruzhao, a researcher with the Infectious Disease Division of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said at a news conference held by the National Health and Health Commission on Feb. 2 that "the majority of sanitation workers, bus drivers and other personnel should wear masks regularly while on duty. " Subsequently, circulars on protecting sanitation workers against epidemic diseases have been issued in many areas of the country.

Prior to this, some people have noticed the sanitation workers of epidemic prevention predicament, "Mask Shenzhen" , "mask Beijing" , "Mask Fuzhou" and other voluntary activities have emerged.

Wang Chuyan is one of the seven heads of the "Shenzhen Mask" and a high school sophomore. The team's seven leaders, with an average age of 16, may be the youngest team in the nation's mask campaign. On the morning of the New Year's Eve, Wang Chuyan accidentally found a "mask Shenzhen" push on Wechat, had participated in a number of volunteer activities she was eager to join the team.

After a preliminary understanding of the situation, she found that the sanitation workers epidemic prevention situation is not optimistic. "there are nine outsourcing companies in Shenzhen, one of them is a little better, and each person can basically share one mask on average every day. Other companies, generally, give out one or two masks before the Chinese New Year and don't manage them for several days after, " Wang said. The Shenzhen Municipal Bureau of Sanitation told her that the government had allocated 10,000 masks to sanitation workers, but that was a drop in the bucket for the daily demand of the city's nine sanitation companies and more than 80,000 workers.

On February 4, the Zhuhai Environmental Health Association published a paper on the public, "paying attention to the problem of the shortage of sanitation workers' epidemic prevention and control materials, " which attracted the attention of junior Qiao Longxuan. He immediately drew on his classmates and friends to set up the "Zhuhai Mask" project, hoping to do a little for the sanitation workers in Zhuhai who lack anti-epidemic materials.

With the help of the Zhuhai Environmental Health Association and the city's appearance center in Zhuhai, the team collected questionnaires from 2,204 sanitation workers on Feb. 11. The results showed that 1,600 sanitation workers could not buy masks, nearly 800 people use paper masks, cotton masks, hand sanitizer, protective gloves and other materials are also extremely scarce.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Seventy-two percent of the sanitation workers surveyed could not buy masks

"I was really shocked when I saw the data, " said Liang Zhicheng, a junior at Zhuhai, one of the city's leaders. There are more than 10,000 sanitation workers in Zhuhai, and so much demand can not be met.

A rocky road to fund-raising

Founded on January 24, issued the first round of donation notice on January 25, January 27 at noon, "Mask Shenzhen" announced the completion of the first round of fundraising, a total of nearly 1,000 people from about 38,000 yuan charity, exceeded the original target of 30,000 yuan.

To avoid legal disputes, the Shenzhen Mask team also consulted five lawyers on matters related to the charity law, and on the advice of the lawyers, they started contacting charities and ngos. On January 27, Shenzhen Radio, Film and Television Public Welfare Foundation relevant person in charge of the initiative contacted them.

"The foundation usually uses the reimbursement system, but since we are students, we don't necessarily have such an advance in our home, and the factory may not be able to issue invoices during special periods, " Ms. Wang said. After two days of consultation, "Mask Shenzhen" finally decided to establish a relationship with the Public Welfare Foundation of Shenzhen Radio, film, co-management and supervision of fund flows and separate audit.

On January 29, "Mask Shenzhen" conducted another fund-raising. After two rounds of fund-raising, "Mask Shenzhen" raised more than 73,000 yuan.

On the other hand, the late start of the "mask Zhuhai" fund-raising journey but twists and turns.

"In fact, there has always been a very difficult problem, that is, how can we get more people to help us promote it. " In order to get more people to pay attention to Zhuhai sanitation workers, liang and five other teammates tried everything: contacting the official public accounts of universities in Zhuhai, the Zhuhai Charity Federation and the Shenzhen Radio and Television Foundation, but were mostly "declined. ".

The Zhuhai Charity Federation told Liang by telephone that because of the severity of the epidemic, it was under the unified command of the city or the province to mobilize materials and use donations, and it did not have the energy to cooperate with individuals or organizations at the moment. Radio and Television Foundation also declined for the same reason, "Mask Zhuhai" cooperation needs.

To make matters worse, on February 16, the public account of the "Zhuhai Mask" was blocked, and some enthusiasts who wanted to donate told Liang: "The push link is not available. "

Qiao Longxuan and Liang Zhicheng guess is because the mask assistant micro-signal only recently to carry out real-name authentication, and a short time and high-frequency accepted donations, resulting in the micro-channel platform to freeze the collection function, bound by the public account has also been temporarily blocked. They immediately lodged a complaint with wechat customer service and are still awaiting the outcome.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Zhuhai Mask" is encouraged by enthusiastic citizens (photo provided by interviewees) 

Even if propagandizes, the docking aspect rough unceasing, "the mask Zhuhai" the team also encountered many warm feelings. After seeing their push, the left Atrium charity group and handshaking charity group contacted them and offered to help spread the word. They also shared their experience of running charity projects with the head of "Mask Zhuhai" .

"Mask Zhuhai" team has also been encouraged by many caring people. The most impressive is Zhang Bo, 55, who has worked in sanitation in Guangzhou for 21 years and calls himself a "sanitation graduate" with a sense of humor.

Not long ago, Zhang Bogang donated 500 yuan to Hubei and could not provide more money to support the "mask Zhuhai" project. He was somewhat annoyed: "If only it had been earlier, the money would not have been sent to Hubei. " During the epidemic, zhang Bo also played a joke on the other sanitation workers to ease the tension: "every sanitation workers bring their own 'sterilizing' organs, the virus to the sanitation workers on the body are digested by this organ, you can rest assured that is, but still pay attention to protection. "

After 21 years in the field, Zhang Bo received a lot of glances and was surprised to learn that a group of college students were helping the sanitation workers raise money to buy masks. Zhang Bo was more grateful and moved. "I'm touched that they care about us, the sanitation workers. "

Although the funds raised are still some way from the goal of 30,000 yuan, Liang and his teammates do not feel depressed, "No matter how much we raise, we've done everything we can to get people to pay attention to this group, and I think the meaning of the event has been achieved. "

Over 400 calls, one by one

Under the epidemic situation, the supply of medical protection materials is tight, many manufacturers have been requisitioned specifically for Hubei epidemic areas. Drugstores on the streets are posting "mask sold out" notices, making it difficult to get qualified respirators for the thousands of sanitation workers in Shenzhen and Zhuhai.

Zhao Chonglin and the "mask Zhuhai" team-mates in the major wholesale platform search results, and then to post, friends circle, Weibo, finally got a list of epidemic prevention materials manufacturers. The form was long, with contact details for more than 400 manufacturers, and it took Zhao two hours to call them one by one.

However, most of the calls could not be connected, and the calls were either hung up or, after listening to Zhao's intentions, dropped off as "no" . Zhao became anxious. "A lot of our supplies are either requisitioned or we have to buy 50,000 or 100,000 or more, and we can only buy a few thousand masks at a time. "

On the other hand, it is very difficult to find a manufacturer with "three certificates and one standard" , and a large quantity of inferior masks in the market also bring trouble to Zhao Chonglin's material purchase. In order to let the sanitation workers use the mask with confidence, Zhao Chonglin before the purchase will also require manufacturers to show proof of production qualifications, material photos.

Mask and other protective materials in short supply, usually sell 1 yuan are slightly expensive general medical mask prices are rising exponentially. "The purchase price has been changing and the supply of goods has been changing. If we don't negotiate a deposit price with the manufacturer today, the mask may not be available the next day, " Zhao told nandu weekly, "When we first learned about it a week ago, masks were about 3.50 yuan a piece. Now most manufacturers are selling them for 4.50 yuan. "

In contrast, the early start of the "mask Shenzhen" is much luckier. At the end of January, Wang Chuyan and teammates contacted the two producers of anti-epidemic supplies gave the mask price of 0.5-0.7 yuan, and then contacted the manufacturers, the price rose to 2.5-3.8 yuan. They received more than 73,000 yuan in donations for the purchase of more than 20,000 medical masks and 1.5 tons of 84 disinfectant, of which nearly 2,000 masks were donated by caring people.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Sanitation Company will "Mask Shenzhen" collection of anti-epidemic materials distributed to sanitation workers. (photo provided by interviewee)

From January 29 to February 17, five or six consignments arrived in Shenzhen. The first 520 masks donated by Shenzhen enterprises went to the sanitation workers. On the morning of the 29th, Zhong Muteng of the distribution team rented a van from Luohu district of Shenzhen to Dongguan to pick up the masks and deliver them to a sanitation company in Longgang District.

"there were about 20 sanitation workers waiting, " Zhong said as he showed the workers how to wear the masks he had learned from the factory in the morning, and highlighted a few caveats. "I felt a little sick at the time... the sanitation workers still needed attention, " Zhong said.

The "Mask Shenzhen" team sent the masks to the Shenzhen Environmental Health Management Office. (photo provided by interviewee)

At present, "Mask Shenzhen" project has entered the final stage, the last batch of a total of 12,000 masks will be issued in the near future.

"Zhuhai Mask" has also raised about 14,900 yuan for charity. It is reported that the left Atrium Public Welfare Organization is interested in providing financial support to it, united International College (UIC Luoping Foundation) Foundation said it is willing to fund "mask Zhuhai" 3000 yuan, epidemic prevention supplies are still in talks.

Recalling half a month of busyness, Wang Chuyan sighed, "I'm glad I can help. " When the reporter contacted Wei Qiang, a sanitation worker in Shenzhen again, "We have a mask! " He shouted at the other end of the phone. "The unit has also been issued and he has bought one. "

(at the request of the interviewee, Wei Qiang and Xue Hua Hua were given pseudonyms
